<A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uruadinstoutheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ruadin Stoutheart</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.kc.rr.com/matts50l/icon.JPG" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/2/02 11:17:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15136.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proc Buffs (Divine Might, Instrument of Nife, etc)</span><hr size=1> A great compromise in the situation where there is 50/50 live/undead is using boon of the garou from an enchanter.  The proc is meager (35dmg/35hp heal), but it works versus all and most importantly to me it raises attack by 40.  So not only am I doing a small dmg/heal I am getting a higher attack rating...and I don't have to worry about which self proc to use :P<br>
<br>
But really its hard to say which to use of our own.  I always try to use Instrument of Nife whenever able, but it always seems to me as soon as I am geared for undead killing there is a huge streak of live things and it bugs me to not be getting extra damage from the proc I used.  So generally I will use DM since it works versus all.  Besides to me 65dmg versus all is better then nice damage versus undead only, since a lot of spawn situations like that have large streaks of live.<br>
<br>
What really needs to happen is another DM style quest at 60, giving us a minimum of 100dmg proc versus all, preferably around 120dmg  with the 30min duration of IoN.  <br>
<br>
Also even though IoN is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  very</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> nice as it is, its a level 30 spell, perhaps we need a upgrade by 60 for that as well...maybe not increase the damage much but maybe the percentage of procs and duration.  Something like 273dmg(Expel undead equiv on proc hehe)/% 10 more proc chance/45 minute duration. Afterall Verant is making us the undead slayers are they not?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    Maybe I am wrong about this (since its a very nice dmg addition already), or maybe Verant should have made it a higher level spell, but it seems a class specific level 30 spell should have a upgrade by 60 to me.<br>
<br>
Also another note, I know that dex is not supposed to greatly change proc rates of our spell added procs, but I have also witnessed when I have over 200 dex I will more likely go into &quot;proc frenzy's&quot; as I like to call them where I get upwards of 6 procs in a row.  This never happens with my normal dex around 120's, most that I ever get consecutively without dex buffs seems to be 3 top's, maybe its just a incredible coincidence though.<br>
<br>
 <p><B>Ruadin Stoutheart, Crusader of Brell</B><BR>
