<br>
A stupidly high amount of the time, if I waited more than half my weapon's delay (which is 39) to cast Holy Might so that  when I finished casting I would immediately swing, it would very frequently (more than half the time) proc or try to proc IoN on that swing. It even happened twice or three times in a row one fight. Aside from those times, I only rarely procced. (although one time I did 1k damage in the first 2 rounds of combat against an undead MoB... fun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  But I did also cast Holy Might....) <p><font><font size=3><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45984>Balidin</a>,</font> The Evilbasher</b><BR><font color=red><i>Paladin of the 4900th LFG</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utaliewin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taliewin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 248<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/2/02 2:43:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15136.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proc Buffs (Divine Might, Instrument of Nife, etc)</span><hr size=1> With something like 120 DEX, I got 7 procs of IoN in one fight once (unfortunately one only hit for 29dam <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), against the Ghoul Lord.  With the same DEX I have gone through two whole fights without a proc (though unusual).  <br>
<br>
Due to gear changes my DEX is now something like 103, and the reduction I have seen in procs (based on observation, not parsing) is small, though I have still noticed it. I was getting on average I would say nearly two procs per fight, whereas now it would be closer to one (vs. LGuk Frogloks).<br>
